race.comment: WACO KID (2) is searching for his fourth win in a row, too good again last time at Sandown Lakeside when overhauling Itsukushima. This is a bit tougher again but rising to 1800m looks in his favour and he's hard to knock in this sort of form. MR BANNOCK (7) ran a good race first up at Geelong over 1512m, getting home strongly for second. More ground here will suit although it's likely he'll improve out of this as well. TAKA SPEED (1) has won both this time in, making it 3 wins from 5 overall starts. He's progressive and will be up on speed again. CANARA (10) is going okay and has each way claims.
